<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key: F major (1 flat: Bb). Hymn has two parallel A-sections (bars 1-4, 5-8) then a B-section (9-16).
- A-section pattern: IV → F → C → F. LH uses open "334" voicings (root-5th-octave-3rd).
- B-section (bars 9-15): richer voicings — Am as substitute for A major (diatonic ③m).
- Bar 7: BbΔ7 (Bbmaj7) for warmth — all-diatonic 4-note voicing in LH.
- Bar 13: FΔ7 (Fmaj7) mid-phrase — the FΔ7 annotation in the ABC is used literally.
- Bar 14: C7 (C dominant 7th, C2 E3 G3 Bb3) for strong pre-cadential tension.
- Bar 15: Final cadence Gm→F→Gm7→C with full quarter-note LH motion.
  - Quartal "44" voicing on Gm (G2 C3 F3) for modern color.
  - Gm7 (G2 Bb2 D3 F3) rich 4-note bass.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2 RH: suspension figure A4→G4 (from IV to V) mirrors melody's long G4.
- Bar 9 RH: descending E5→C5→Bb4→A4 against ascending LH bass A2→C2→D2 — contrary motion.
- Bar 15 RH: complete stepwise descent D5→C5→Bb4→G4 over cadential LH circle-of-4ths.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-4: Light opening — half-note LH, 2-note RH. Establishes F major with IV→I motion.
- Bars 5-8: Repeat section — slightly varied RH (ascending arpeggio bar 5), BbΔ7 for warmth (bar 7).
- Bars 9-14: B-section — busier harmonic rhythm (3-4 chords/bar), Am and E° color chords, climbing RH.
- Bars 15-16: Final cadence — full quarter-note LH (Gm7→C→F), descending RH suspension line.
-->
